        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Controller_Dispatcher::addControllerDirectory() checks directories in the order that they were added.  On the other hand, Zend_Controller_RewriteRouter::route() matches routes in reverse.  Cascading (checking in reverse) seems more correct to me for directory routes.\n\n---        foreach ($directories as $directory) {\n+++        foreach (array_reverse($directories) as $directory) {"
